\cos (2a)=\cos ^{2}a-\sin ^{2}a.
\cos (2a)=\cos ^{2}a-\sin ^{2}a=\cos ^{2}a-1+\cos^2a=2\cos ^{2}a-1,
\cos ^{2}a=\dfrac{1+\cos (2a)}{2}.
